By Sheila Offiong
The Royal school of Educational therapy foundation (RSETF) Abuja organised an art exhibition to celebrate the achievements of its students. The foundation offers Educational therapy and related services for children and adults with developmental disabilities such as Autism Spectrum Disorder, Down Syndrome, Dyslexia and Intellectual Disabilities. The exhibition showcased the talents and intelligence of the children. NANTV crew was at hand to capture the highlights of the event. 